// =============================================================================
// Bitwise — 32-bit AND / OR / XOR on non-negative integers. EXPENSIVE.
// =============================================================================
//
// Sutra has no native bitwise OPERATOR (`&` / `|` are the fuzzy three-valued
// LOGICAL ops; `<<` / `>>` do not parse). True bitwise is a substrate
// computation: decompose each operand into its 32 bit-planes, apply the
// per-bit logic, and recombine.
//
// ── Why this is substrate-pure (not scalar extraction) ──────────────────────
//
// A number-vector carries its value on AXIS_REAL and zero on every other
// axis. `_VSA.band/bor/bxor` broadcast the WHOLE vector against a (32,)
// powers-of-two tensor to form a (32, dim) bit-plane stack:
//
//   bit_i = floor(x / 2^i) - 2·floor(x / 2^(i+1))
//
// (every non-real axis decomposes to all-zero bits, so they stay zero), apply
// the per-bit boolean as element-wise tensor arithmetic —
//
//   AND  = a·b          OR  = a + b - a·b          XOR = a + b - 2·a·b
//
// — and recombine with a powers-weighted sum back into a number-vector. All
// torch tensor ops, no host scalar, no numpy. See codegen_pytorch.py
// `_bits_of` / `band` / `bor` / `bxor`.
//
// Domain: non-negative integers < 2^32 (the WASM machine's unsigned 32-bit
// values). Shifts are NOT here — `x << k` / `x >> k` are exact arithmetic
// identities (`x * 2^k` / `Math.floor(x / 2^k)`) that callers emit directly.

class Bits extends vector {

    // Bitwise AND — `a & b` over 32-bit unsigned integers.
    static intrinsic method number band(number a, number b);

    // Bitwise OR — `a | b`.
    static intrinsic method number bor(number a, number b);

    // Bitwise XOR — `a ^ b`.
    static intrinsic method number bxor(number a, number b);
}
